{"type":"message","id":"1f17f317","parentId":"61625e0b","timestamp":"2026-04-14T00:35:31.426Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have some data. Let me compile what I found:\n\nFrom the search results:\n1. **Nasdaq**: The search mentions Nasdaq 8 consecutive wins up to April 10 (22,902.89 on April 10). But one result mentions \"美股13日涨跌不一\" - but that seems to be about February 12, 2026 (2026年2月12日), not April 13. Let me check more carefully.\n\nActually, looking at the first search result more carefully, it says:\n- April 10 data: Nasdaq 22,902.89 (+0.35%), SOX 8,889.83 (+2.31%)\n\n\n- The data cutoff mentioned is \"美股：2026-04-10收盘 / 亚太：2026-04-13早盘\"\n\nFrom the second search about SOX on April 13, I'm seeing some conflicting data points - one source shows SOX opening at 8,873.3 with a high of 9,044.4 and closing at 9,039.5 for a gain of 1.68%, while another lists it at 8,949.8 with a 0.67% increase, so I need to clarify which April 13 figure is accurate.\n\nThe data cutoff for the first source appears to be April 10, which explains why April 13 doesn't show up there. I should search for the actual April 13 closing prices for both Nasdaq and SOX to get the most reliable numbers.","thinkingSignature":"2264a9014acd674279baf64d11d7ef38822c0af7aedef73391f955ef19999e2b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fni05a67ytk3_1","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"nasdaq composite close April 13 2026"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11055,"output":348,"cacheRead":18540,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29943,"cost":{"input":0.0033165,"output":0.00041759999999999996,"cacheRead":0.0011124,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0048465}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776126916721,"responseId":"062cbec4c24458597924c39f97be9c9f"}}
