{"type":"message","id":"cbacbe10","parentId":"365a51d6","timestamp":"2026-04-14T00:35:47.631Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I'm having trouble getting the exact April 13 Nasdaq close. Let me try to fetch the data from a specific source. Let me try to access the Nasdaq index history page directly, or try another approach.\n\nFrom the first search, I got some useful info:\n- SOX on April 13: 9039.5 (+1.68%) from one source, or 8949.8 (+0.67%) from another source\n- The first source (wantgoo.com) shows SOX April 13: open 8873.3, high 9044.4, low 8838.5, close 9039.5, change +1.68%\n\n\n- This is more reliable data\n\nFor Nasdaq, I'm still trying to pin down the exact close on April 13, though I know April 10 was 22,902.89. The first search mentions geopolitical tensions from US-Iran negotiations and oil price impacts on markets, which might explain the volatility, but I need to find the specific Nasdaq figure.\n\nLooking at more recent market data, it appears Nasdaq may have broken its 8-day winning streak on April 13. I'm seeing some conflicting signals across different sources - one mentions Nasdaq Composite trading down 0.22% on April 13, though the date reference seems unclear. Let me dig deeper into the historical records to clarify the exact closing values for both Nasdaq and SOX on April 13.","thinkingSignature":"478b72bd5fc632b944f0eb403a7dfee35c006ff9f58de79949652a7e443eeb75"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zt8f53lnqrwr_1","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://indexes.nasdaqomx.com/Index/History/COMP","extractMode":"text","maxChars":5000}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":19203,"output":358,"cacheRead":18540,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38101,"cost":{"input":0.005760899999999999,"output":0.0004296,"cacheRead":0.0011124,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.007302899999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776126934054,"responseId":"062cbed645e0f6d24306