{"type":"message","id":"c5848b05","parentId":"2a84f165","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:57:28.882Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the cron status shows:\n- enabled: true\n- jobs: 0\n- nextWakeAtMs: null\n\nBut there's a gateway pairing issue. The cron tool is using the built-in tool which seems to work (it returned status). But the user is saying \"定时任务无法设置\" - they can't set timed tasks.\n\nWait, let me re-read. The user says \"尝试修复定时任务无法设置的问题\" - they want to fix the issue where timed tasks can't be set. \n\nThe cron tool itself returned status OK. Let me try to add a simple test cron job to see if it works.\n\nActually, the cron tool returned a valid response with jobs:0, so the cron system itself is working. \n\nI'm wondering if the issue is with how the user is trying to set up these tasks - maybe they're hitting limitations in the ACP coding session's cron implementation, or perhaps the problem is specific to certain types of cron configurations rather than a system-wide failure.\n\nLet me test the cron tool directly to see if it actually works.","thinkingSignature":"a41b87fd8403bfee2c6cb82c5df03c18d7ba02d2ab826e7d636128bb6127ba4f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_aoan8gboi411_1","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"list"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":26780,"output":241,"cacheRead":18540,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45561,"cost":{"input":0.008034,"output":0.0002892,"cacheRead":0.0011124,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.009435599999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776135439149,"responseId":"062ce00f1e5a23e6b5e1edee819e9473"}}
