{"type":"message","id":"d8fcc20e","parentId":"5c8c5dcc","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:58:25.248Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The jobs.json file is empty `[]`. The cron tool's `list` works (it reads the file directly) but `add` fails because it goes through the gateway RPC.\n\nLet me check if there's a way to add jobs by directly writing to the jobs.json file. First, let me look at the schema of jobs.json to understand the format.\n\nThe cron tool's `add` action failed with \"pairing required\". This is because the cron tool's add/update/remove actions use the gateway RPC, while list/status read directly from the file.\n\nLet me look at the jobs.json schema by examining the cron tool's add schema more carefully. The job schema I used earlier was:\n```\n{\n  \"name\": \"test-job\",\n  \"schedule\": { \"kind\": \"cron\", \"expr\": \"*/5 * * * *\", \"tz\": \"Asia/Shanghai\" },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n  \"payload\": { \"kind\": \"agentTurn\", \"message\": \"...\" }\n}\n```\n\nSince the file-based approach won't work for cron add operations and the cron tool requires gateway pairing for modifications, I need to check the node-connect skill to understand how to properly establish that pairing connection.","thinkingSignature":"2c4a47a8342b8906cfdc401b656c4882ecef6631e220af7fcee4cef1b045ec8e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zpkeh18k7cab_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/skills/node-connect/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":28971,"output":287,"cacheRead":18540,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47798,"cost":{"input":0.008691299999999999,"output":0.00034439999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0011124,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.010148099999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776135496067,"responseId":"062ce0485a64aa7e7bdc70a9182c579c"}}
