{"type":"message","id":"d15e7a39","parentId":"3dcc6a25","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:58:38.570Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The skill doesn't exist at that path. Let me look at the cron tool's error more carefully.\n\nThe error is: \"gateway closed (1008): pairing required\"\n\nThis happens when trying to use `cron add`. The `cron list/status` reads directly from the file.\n\nI wonder if the issue is that the gateway is in \"pairing required\" mode and the cron tool is using a different authentication mechanism.\n\nLooking at the status output: \"Gateway: bind=loopback (127.0.0.1), port=18789 (service args)\"\n\nThe gateway is accessible locally. The cron tool is a built-in tool that should be able to interact with the gateway.\n \nSo the built-in cron tool bypasses the file system entirely and makes direct RPC calls to the gateway instead. The \"pairing required\" error suggests the gateway has pairing mode enabled as a security measure, which means I need to establish a paired connection before the cron tool can create jobs. This is likely intentional—the gateway restricts job creation to paired/authorized clients only.\n\nBut here's what's puzzling me: the main session is already authorized (it's an active conversation), yet the cron tool still fails. Maybe the cron tool uses a separate internal API key or credentials that aren't the same as the main session's authentication. I should check the openclaw logs to see what's actually happening when the cron tool tries to connect.","thinkingSignature":"b26a5355f16426e5578f2ca59f76230d22926515261bad50ae18be4d590db47e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_30xu5ivo3x0a_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -50 /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-14.log 2>&1 | grep -E \"(cron|pairing|error|Error)\" | tail -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":29317,"output":346,"cacheRead":18540,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":48203,"cost":{"input":0.0087951,"output":0.00041519999999999995,"cacheRead":0.0011124,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.010322699999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776135505261,"responseId":"062ce051d96f42698f327bb4e7613d86"}}
