{"type":"message","id":"7d43b1a0","parentId":"eeeaca36","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:59:05.946Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the gateway configuration:\n- `mode: \"local\"` - gateway runs locally\n- `auth.mode: \"token\"` - uses token auth\n- `bind: \"loopback\"` - only accessible locally\n- `controlUi.allowInsecureAuth: true` - allows insecure auth for the control UI\n\nThe issue is that the cron tool is trying to use the gateway RPC, and the gateway says \"pairing required\". This might be because the cron tool's internal client isn't properly authenticated with the gateway token.\n\nLet me check if there's a specific pairing step needed. Looking at the gateway config, it has `auth.mode: \"token\"` and there's a token. The cron tool might need this token to be passed somehow.\n \nThe error message indicates the gateway is enforcing a pairing requirement that's preventing the cron tool from connecting. I'm noticing the system prompt mentions authorized senders, which suggests there's an allowlist for sender IDs - this might be relevant to why the pairing is failing.\n\nLet me check if there's a pairing configuration file I can access or if the gateway's local authentication is set up in a way that's blocking the cron tool specifically.","thinkingSignature":"b65435f277bdb8423378d3e6922f0c920faa1abdb3014e9666fe7a96ea3d00a8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j5befxtcpz3u_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /root/.openclaw/agents/ 2>&1 && ls -la /root/.openclaw/gateway* 2>&1 || true"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j5befxtcpz3u_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find /root/.openclaw -name \"*.json\" -path \"*pair*\" -o -name \"pairing*\" -o -name \"known*\" 2>/dev/null | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":33378,"output":349,"cacheRead":18540,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52267,"cost":{"input":0.010013399999999999,"output":0.0