{"type":"message","id":"43df8e59","parentId":"45cb4a61","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:59:17.834Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see there are two paired devices, but neither has full operator.write scope for cron operations. The `openclaw-control-ui` device has `operator.write` scope, but the `gateway-client` device (which is the internal backend client) only has `operator.read` scope.\n\nThe issue is that the cron tool (which runs as a backend/internal client) is trying to use the gateway RPC but it only has `operator.read` scope, not `operator.write` scope which is needed for adding cron jobs.\n\nHowever, looking more carefully at the pairing data:\n- The `openclaw-control-ui` pairing has full scopes including `operator.write` and `operator.pairing`\n- The `gateway-client` pairing only has `operator.read`","thinkingSignature":"ae0f4182a11c599c4c546e34fe0ce4b86a059dcdbe4a7e57643e3378d45cdcd3"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0n3lf2zmq9t5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/agents/main/agents.json 2>&1 || ls -la /root/.openclaw/agents/main/ 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":34705,"output":209,"cacheRead":18540,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53454,"cost":{"input":0.010411499999999999,"output":0.00025079999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0011124,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011774699999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776135549877,"responseId":"062ce07d57f7191463830a0d466d149c"}}
