{"type":"message","id":"27355463","parentId":"12771fa4","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:00:25.724Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The curl requests are getting \"Not Found\". This is expected since the gateway uses WebSocket, not HTTP POST for its RPC interface.\n\nLet me take a different approach. The issue is that `cron add` requires gateway pairing authentication. Let me check if there's a way to approve the pairing or if the cron tool has a built-in way to bypass this for local operations.\n\nActually, let me re-read the error message more carefully:\n- `gateway closed (1008): pairing required`\n\nThis suggests the gateway is rejecting the connection because it requires pairing. The pairing requirement might be a security measure for certain types of operations.\n\nLet me look at the OpenClaw docs to understand:\n1. Why the cron tool requires pairing\n2. How to configure the gateway to allow cron operations\n\nLet me also look at the automation/cron-jobs.md file.","thinkingSignature":"34f114951f86ab9da35b007e2d45259c2d5411c997b90066db64677b92a6574a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_0q7xgvz123p9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls /usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/automation/ 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41093,"output":213,"cacheRead":18540,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59846,"cost":{"input":0.0123279,"output":0.0002556,"cacheRead":0.0011124,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.013695899999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776135619389,"responseId":"062ce0c39c47f39def1382a12905408e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ca173062","parentId":"27355463","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:00:25.818Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0q7xgvz123p9_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"auth-monitoring.md\nclawflow.md\ncron-jobs.md\ncron-vs-heartbeat.md\ngmail-pubsub.md\nhooks.md\nindex.md\npoll.md\nstanding-orders.md\ntaskflow.md\ntasks.md\ntroubleshooting.md\nwebhook.md"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":88,"aggregated":"auth-monitoring.md\nclawflow.md\ncron-jobs.md\ncron-vs-heartbeat.md\ngmail-pubsub.md\nhooks.md\nindex.md\npoll.md\nstanding-orders.md\ntaskflow.md\ntasks.md\ntroubleshooting.md\nwebhook.md","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776135625817}}
{"type":"message","id":"2949a783","parentId":"ca173062","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:00:29.056Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the cron-jobs.md to understand how cron is supposed to work and what the pairing requirement means.","thinkingSignature":"bdf83826335fb61dcaa8db2dc3bce2585d15c7c57bf261288c0113a555520a28"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4k613g6430ej_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/usr/lib/node_modules/openclaw/docs/automation/cron-jobs.md","limit":80}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41375,"output":73,"cacheRead":18540,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59988,"cost":{"input":0.0124125,"output":0.0000876,"cacheRead":0.0011124,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0136125}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776135625823,"responseId":"062ce0c9e59ac33c230a11f24f933cc6"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5dbc80c2","parentId":"2949a783","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:00:29.065Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4k613g6430ej_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"Scheduled jobs, webhooks, and Gmail PubSub triggers for the Gateway scheduler\"\nread_when:\n  - Scheduling background jobs or wakeups\n  - Wiring external triggers (webhooks, Gmail) into OpenClaw\n  - Deciding between heartbeat and cron for scheduled tasks\ntitle: \"Scheduled Tasks\"\n---\n\n# Scheduled Tasks (Cron)\n\nCron is the Gateway's built-in scheduler. It persists jobs, wakes the agent at the right time, and can deliver output back to a chat channel or webhook endpoint.\n\n## Quick start\n\n```bash\n# Add a one-shot reminder\nopenclaw cron add \\\n  --name \"Reminder\" \\\n  --at \"2026-02-01T16:00:00Z\" \\\n  --session main \\\n  --system-event \"Reminder: check the cron docs draft\" \\\n  --wake now \\\n  --delete-after-run\n\n# Check your jobs\nopenclaw cron list\n\n# See run history\nopenclaw cron runs --id <job-id>\n```\n\n## How cron works\n\n- Cron runs **inside the Gateway** process (not inside the model).\n- Jobs persist at `~/.openclaw/cron/jobs.json` so restarts do not lose schedules.\n- All cron executions create [background task](/automation/tasks) records.\n- One-shot jobs (`--at`) auto-delete after success by default.\n- Isolated cron runs best-effort close tracked browser tabs/processes for their `cron:<jobId>` session when the run completes, so detached browser automation does not leave orphaned processes behind.\n- Isolated cron runs also guard against stale acknowledgement replies. If the\n  first result is just an interim status update (`on it`, `pulling everything\ntogether`, and similar hints) and no descendant subagent run is still\n  responsible for the final answer, OpenClaw re-prompts once for the actual\n  result before delivery.\n\n<a id=\"maintenance\"></a>\n\nTask reconciliation for cron is runtime-owned: an active cron task stays live while the\ncron runtime still tracks that job as running, even if an old child session row still exists.\nOnce the runtime stops owning the job and the 5-minute grace window expires, maintenance can\nmark the task `lost`.\n\n## Schedule types\n\n| Kind    | CLI flag  | Description                                             |\n| ------- | --------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |\n| `at`    | `--at`    | One-shot timestamp (ISO 8601 or relative like `20m`)    |\n| `every` | `--every` | Fixed interval                                          |\n| `cron`  | `--cron`  | 5-field or 6-field cron expression with optional `--tz` |\n\nTimestamps without a timezone are treated as UTC. Add `--tz America/New_York` for local wall-clock scheduling.\n\nRecurring top-of-hour expressions are automatically staggered by up to 5 minutes to reduce load spikes. Use `--exact` to force precise timing or `--stagger 30s` for an explicit window.\n\n### Day-of-month and day-of-week use OR logic\n\nCron expressions are parsed by [croner](https://github.com/Hexagon/croner). When both the day-of-month and day-of-week fields are non-wildcard, croner matches when **either** field matches — not both. This is standard Vixie cron behavior.\n\n```\n# Intended: \"9 AM on the 15th, only if it's a Monday\"\n# Actual:   \"9 AM on every 15th, AND 9 AM on every Monday\"\n0 9 15 * 1\n```\n\nThis fires ~5–6 times per month instead of 0–1 times per month. OpenClaw uses Croner's default OR behavior here. To require both conditions, use Croner's `+` day-of-week modifier (`0 9 15 * +1`) or schedule on one field and guard the other in your job's prompt or command.\n\n## Execution styles\n\n| Style           | `--session` value   | Runs in                  | Best for                        |\n| --------------- | ------------------- | ------------------------ | ------------------------------- |\n\n[345 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776135629063}}
{"type":"message","id":"fba72394","parentId":"5dbc80c2","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:00:42.358Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see that cron jobs are managed via `openclaw cron` CLI commands. Let me try using the CLI to add a cron job instead of the tool. The CLI might work differently than the tool.But wait - the cron tool's `add` action went through the gateway RPC and failed. The CLI would also connect to the gateway. Let me try the CLI to see if it works differently.Actually, let me first understand the architecture better. The cron tool is a built-in tool that connects to the gateway. The `list`/`status` operations might work by reading the file directly, while `add`/`update`/`remove` operations go through the gateway RPC.Let me try using the openclaw CLI to add a cron job and see if it has the same issue.","thinkingSignature":"d09746692a1f770f73908d9324ed1be3c45557d17ebea8a1674ba909f363e14f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xlktuh2f7qsl_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron add --name \"test\" --every \"5m\" --session isolated --agent-turn \"test\" 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42320,"output":223,"cacheRead":18540,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61083,"cost":{"input":0.012695999999999999,"output":0.0002676,"cacheRead":0.0011124,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014075999999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776135629069,"responseId":"062ce0cd2b7ecd2b37c5f3cf69a6a769"}}
