{"type":"message","id":"37537414","parentId":"08b738fa","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:00:46.905Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check the correct syntax for the openclaw cron add command.","thinkingSignature":"f7594537f9a92cff7e0f92ae64aa05e400863df2d0c1ad6b591b8ba6fa2459ae"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_irmpe8lcqxut_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron add --help 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42573,"output":59,"cacheRead":18540,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61172,"cost":{"input":0.0127719,"output":0.0000708,"cacheRead":0.0011124,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.013955099999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776135644368,"responseId":"062ce0dccb7604a369aa0984afc80ed8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0d978b03","parentId":"37537414","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:00:49.982Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_irmpe8lcqxut_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.12 (1c0672b) — Your task has been queued; your dignity has been deprecated.\n\nUsage: openclaw cron add|create [options]\n\nAdd a cron job\n\nOptions:\n  --account <id>         Channel account id for delivery (multi-account setups)\n  --agent <id>           Agent id for this job\n  --announce             Announce summary to a chat (subagent-style) (default:\n                         false)\n  --at <when>            Run once at time (ISO with offset, or +duration). Use\n                         --tz for offset-less datetimes\n  --best-effort-deliver  Do not fail the job if delivery fails (default: false)\n  --channel <channel>    Delivery channel (last|<channel-id>) (default: \"last\")\n  --cron <expr>          Cron expression (5-field or 6-field with seconds)\n  --delete-after-run     Delete one-shot job after it succeeds (default: false)\n  --deliver              Deprecated (use --announce). Announces a summary to a\n                         chat.\n  --description <text>   Optional description\n  --disabled             Create job disabled (default: false)\n  --every <duration>     Run every duration (e.g. 10m, 1h)\n  --exact                Disable cron staggering (set stagger to 0) (default:\n                         false)\n  --expect-final         Wait for final response (agent) (default: false)\n  -h, --help             Display help for command\n  --json                 Output JSON (default: false)\n  --keep-after-run       Keep one-shot job after it succeeds (default: false)\n  --light-context        Use lightweight bootstrap context for agent jobs\n                         (default: false)\n  --message <text>       Agent message payload\n  --model <model>        Model override for agent jobs (provider/model or alias)\n  --name <name>          Job name\n  --no-deliver           Disable announce delivery and skip main-session summary\n  --session <target>     Session target (main|isolated)\n  --session-key <key>    Session key for job routing (e.g.\n                         agent:my-agent:my-session)\n  --stagger <duration>   Cron stagger window (e.g. 30s, 5m)\n  --system-event <text>  System event payload (main session)\n  --thinking <level>     Thinking level for agent jobs\n                         (off|minimal|low|medium|high|xhigh)\n  --timeout <ms>         Timeout in ms (default: \"30000\")\n  --timeout-seconds <n>  Timeout seconds for agent jobs\n  --to <dest>            Delivery destination (E.164, Telegram chatId, or\n                         Discord channel/user)\n  --token <token>        Gateway token (if required)\n  --tools <csv>          Comma-separated tool allow-list (e.g. exec,read,write)\n  --tz <iana>            Timezone for cron expressions (IANA) (default: \"\")\n  --url <url>            Gateway WebSocket URL (defaults to gateway.remote.url\n                         when configured)\n  --wake <mode>          Wake mode (now|next-heartbeat) (default: \"now\")"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3070,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.12 (1c0672b) — Your task has been queued; your dignity has been deprecated.\n\nUsage: openclaw cron add|create [options]\n\nAdd a cron job\n\nOptions:\n  --account <id>         Channel account id for delivery (multi-account setups)\n  --agent <id>           Agent id for this job\n  --announce             Announce summary to a chat (subagent-style) (default:\n                         false)\n  --at <when>            Run once at time (ISO with offset, or +duration). Use\n                         --tz for offset-less datetimes\n  --best-effort-deliver  Do not fail the job if delivery fails (default: false)\n  --channel <channel>    Delivery channel (last|<channel-id>) (default: \"last\")\n  --cron <expr>          Cron expression (5-field or 6-field with seconds)\n  --delete-after-run     Delete one-shot job after it succeeds (default: false)\n  --deliver              Deprecated (use --announce). Announces a summary to a\n                         chat.\n  --description <text>   Optional description\n  --disabled             Create job disabled (default: false)\n  --every <duration>     Run every duration (e.g. 10m, 1h)\n  --exact                Disable cron staggering (set stagger to 0) (default:\n                         false)\n  --expect-final         Wait for final response (agent) (default: false)\n  -h, --help             Display help for command\n  --json                 Output JSON (default: false)\n  --keep-after-run       Keep one-shot job after it succeeds (default: false)\n  --light-context        Use lightweight bootstrap context for agent jobs\n                         (default: false)\n  --message <text>       Agent message payload\n  --model <model>        Model override for agent jobs (provider/model or alias)\n  --name <name>          Job name\n  --no-deliver           Disable announce delivery and skip main-session summary\n  --session <target>     Session target (main|isolated)\n  --session-key <key>    Session key for job routing (e.g.\n                         agent:my-agent:my-session)\n  --stagger <duration>   Cron stagger window (e.g. 30s, 5m)\n  --system-event <text>  System event payload (main session)\n  --thinking <level>     Thinking level for agent jobs\n                         (off|minimal|low|medium|high|xhigh)\n  --timeout <ms>         Timeout in ms (default: \"30000\")\n  --timeout-seconds <n>  Timeout seconds for agent jobs\n  --to <dest>            Delivery destination (E.164, Telegram chatId, or\n                         Discord channel/user)\n  --token <token>        Gateway token (if required)\n  --tools <csv>          Comma-separated tool allow-list (e.g. exec,read,write)\n  --tz <iana>            Timezone for cron expressions (IANA) (default: \"\")\n  --url <url>            Gateway WebSocket URL (defaults to gateway.remote.url\n                         when configured)\n  --wake <mode>          Wake mode (now|next-heartbeat) (default: \"now\")","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776135649980}}
{"type":"message","id":"71e0bcdb","parentId":"0d978b03","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:01:06.698Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see there's a `--token` option for the CLI. This might be the key - the CLI needs a gateway token to authenticate. Let me try with the token from the openclaw.json config.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. The error \"gateway closed (1008): pairing required\" suggests the gateway is rejecting the connection because it requires pairing. This is a WebSocket connection-level issue, not an HTTP authentication issue.\n\nLet me look at the actual cron tool source to understand how it connects to the gateway and why it's getting \"pairing required\".\n\nActually, I should check if the issue is that the gateway has pairing required mode enabled. Let me look at the gateway config more carefully or check the gateway status.\n\nWait - looking back at the gateway config:\n```json\n\"gateway\": {\n    \"mode\": \"local\",\n    \"auth\": {\n      \"mode\": \"token\",\n      \"token\": \"ebcd408d4911376b750bf2b09e86124b140b69bb95362c9a\"\n    },\n```\n\nThe gateway is using token auth mode. But the error says \"pairing required\", not \"invalid token\" or \"unauthorized\". This suggests that the token might not have the right scopes, or the connection itself requires a separate pairing step.\n\nLet me look at the paired.json more carefully. The `gateway-client` device has `operator.read` scope but not `operator.write`. The `openclaw-control-ui` has `operator.write`.\n\nSo the issue is: the cron tool is trying to connect as the `gateway-client` which only has `operator.read` scope, but `cron add` requires `operator.write` scope.\n\nBut wait - the openclaw.json shows the auth mode is \"token\", not \"pairing\". So why is it saying \"pairing required\"?\n\nI think what happening is that the gateway is enforcing pairing for write operations even when using token auth. The `gateway-client` device pairing only has `operator.read` scope, and maybe there's no way to get `operator.write` scope for the internal gateway-client.\n\nLet me try a different approach - maybe I can manually add a job to the jobs.json file directly and see if that works.","thinkingSignature":"b03cbdacd4d32790acd6ca9401edbfd8d8e4fff27f5abd84da5d2245d9952c37"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qlmalziun4w4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('gateway',{}).get('auth',{}))\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43339,"output":522,"cacheRead":18540,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62401,"cost":{"input":0.0130017,"output":0.0006263999999999999,"cacheRead":0.0011124,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.014740499999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776135649989,"responseId":"062ce0e241a5c13118455720a1343877"}}
