{"type":"message","id":"f112274f","parentId":"eb0135de","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:09:23.873Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Line 11 has \"每日（A股交易日）\" which is fine. Line 232 also mentions \"交易日\". Now let me also update the cron job descriptions to clarify \"仅限交易日\" in the name itself.\n\nActually, the cron expression `0 9 * * 1-5` already means Monday to Friday. The limitation is that it can't detect Chinese public holidays. This is a known limitation.\n\nThe user wanted the tasks to only run on trading days. Since we can't express Chinese public holidays in cron, we should:\n1. Keep the current `1-5` expression (which runs Monday to Friday)\n2. Note in the documentation that holidays need manual intervention\n\nBut wait - the original user message said \"不是每天，而是每个交易日\" - the user wants it to run only on trading days. \n\nSince we can't exclude Chinese holidays with cron alone, we need to clarify this constraint with the user and either accept running on all weekdays or handle holiday filtering separately. 实际上，由于A股节假日无法用标准cron表达式处理，最实用的方案是在文档中说明这个限制，同时保持 `1-5` 的配置，让用户在节假日前手动禁用定时任务。","thinkingSignature":"eb9d1c66026f6f22dc41104d6ab4496a42f58eb2373d6e45db3bd20a873c8fbf"},{"type":"text","text":"\n方案文档已更新。cron 表达式 `1-5` 本身代表周一至周五，A股节假日（春节、国庆等调休）无法被自动排除，这是 cron 本身表达式的限制。\n\n**当前方案说明：**\n- `0 9 * * 1-5` = 每个周一至周五执行（09:00）\n- 法定节假日前需**手动暂停任务**（`cron update --jobId xxx --enabled false`）\n\n如果未来需要更智能的节假日过滤，可以考虑：\n1. 在 HEARTBEAT.md 中加入节假日前检查提醒\n2. 或接入中国交易日历 API\n\n方案文档已在\"定时任务执行时间\"部分补充了交易日说明。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":60881,"output":390,"cacheRead":18540,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79811,"cost":{"input":0.0182643,"output":0.000468,"cacheRead":0.0011124,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0198447}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776136149818,"responseId":"062ce2d532724f9840442d175cbf68f9"}}
