{"type":"message","id":"4fa4bf00","parentId":"9ce90f80","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:13:23.218Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No pip available. Let me try a different approach. Let me check if there's a `node` based solution since we have node available. Or maybe there's a way to use the Tencent Finance API to get some kind of market status.Actually, let me think about this differently. The simplest reliable approach might be:\n\n1. A simple script that uses a known working API endpoint\n2. Or a simple Python-only approach using datetime + a holiday lookup table\n\nFor China A-shares:\n- Weekends are definitely non-trading days (Saturday, Sunday)\n- Known holidays in 2026:\n  - New Year's Day: Jan 1 (3 days typically)\n  - Spring Festival: ~Feb 15-21, 2026 (7 days)\n  - Qingming Festival: Apr 4-6, 2026 (3 days)\n  - Labor Day: May 1-3, 2026 (3 days)\n  - Dragon Boat Festival: May 31 - Jun 2, 2026 (3 days)\n  - Mid-Autumn Festival: Sep 25-27, 2026 (3 days)\n  - National Day: Oct 1-7, 2026 (7 days)\n  \nBut this requires maintaining a holiday list manually.\n\nA better approach: Let me try to find a working HTTP API for the trading calendar. Let me search for a simple working endpoint.\n\nActually, let me think about this differently. We could use a web search to get the current trading day info at runtime when the agent runs, or use the Tencent Finance API which we know is working for stock prices.\n\n\nLet me try the simplest approach - use `nohup` or check if node can be used. Actually, I know that Tencent Finance provides some market data. Let me try to use the market status API from Tencent to see if we can detect if the market is open.\n\nWait - actually the simplest thing: just use a web search to check if today is a trading day when the cron job runs. The agent can do a quick web search at the start. But this is not ideal for automation.\n\nLet me try a different HTTP API that I know works for China stock data.","thinki