{"type":"message","id":"b32371bf","parentId":"7ee8a85d","timestamp":"2026-04-14T08:11:29.551Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to install several skills/packages:\n1. agent-browser\n2. find-skills\n3. summarize\n4. skill-creator\n5. tmux\n\nLet me first check what these are. `agent-browser` is likely a browser tool, `find-skills` is for finding skills on ClawdHub, `summarize` is probably a summarization skill, `skill-creator` is for creating skills, and `tmux` is a terminal multiplexer (which would need to be installed via apt/yum).\n\nLet me start by looking at what's available on ClawdHub for these skills, and also install tmux via the system package manager.\n\n\nI'll search ClawdHub for each of the skill packages first to see what's available, then handle tmux as a system installation.","thinkingSignature":"836fb51ada838a7d0fda0662367619ab6691ee70e4f36c2948469b3b32c0675e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lxuebhdnclt2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"which tmux && tmux -V 2>/dev/null || echo \"tmux not installed\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lxuebhdnclt2_2","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"clawhub openclaw agent-browser skill install"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":58,"output":237,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":98449,"totalTokens":98744,"cost":{"input":0.0000174,"output":0.0002844,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.036918375,"total":0.037220175}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776154274233,"responseId":"062d29a22431a78c452a02b56fe8b991"}}
