{"type":"message","id":"dc749b30","parentId":"4e9753eb","timestamp":"2026-04-14T08:11:32.339Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_lxuebhdnclt2_2","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"clawhub openclaw agent-browser skill install\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 2221,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9ad8adf369f59036\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAgent Browser - ClawHub\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9ad8adf369f59036\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://clawhub.ai/matrixy/agent-browser-clawdbot\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3d492b2362dadfce\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe name/description claim headless browser automation; the SKILL.md only instructs the agent to run an agent-browser CLI (navigation, snapshot, refs, sessions, state save/load, network controls). Instructions stay within browser automation scope (open, snapshot, click, fill, state save/load, network routing, execute wait functions). Note: state save/load writes/reads auth JSON (cookies/storage) and the wait/--fn mechanism implies arbitrary JS evaluation in page context — both are expected for automation but can expose credentials or data if misused. It mentions an optional AGENT\\\\_BROWSER\\\\_SESSION env var and uses file paths for state (e.g., auth.json) — these are proportional to a browser automation tool but are locations where sensitive tokens/cookies may be stored. This skill is a set of instructions for using the agent-browser CLI (no code shipped). Before installing or using it: 1) Confirm you trust the agent-browser binary/source (SKILL.md points to a GitHub repo) — installing the CLI will download Chromium and run code on your machine.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"3d492b2362dadfce\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99999404\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5d437c6b9e728e98\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOpenClaw ClawHub Setup Guide: Install, Search, and Manage Skills\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5d437c6b9e728e98\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://fast.io/resources/openclaw-clawhub-setup/\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ecf06c8f018701a4\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nClawHub connects OpenClaw agents to thousands of community skills. ClawHub is the public skill registry for OpenClaw. ClawHub crossed 13,000 published skills in early 2026. ClawHub skill registry search interface. Install the Fastio skill from ClawHub. Free 50 GB, 5 workspaces, 5,000 monthly credits. * List installed skills: `clawhub list`. Fastio is the most popular storage skill on ClawHub, giving agents their own cloud workspaces with 19 tools for file management, search, sharing, and collaboration. Fastio skill page on ClawHub. When in doubt, use `clawhub inspect`  to read the skill contents before installing. Then use `clawhub install ` to add skills to your OpenClaw setup. How many skills are on ClawHub? Where do installed skills go? What is the most popular ClawHub skill? Fastio is one of the most installed storage skills, providing agents with persistent cloud workspaces, file management, and RAG search capabilities. Install the Fastio skill from ClawHub. Free 50 GB, 5 workspaces, 5,000 monthly credits.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ecf06c8f018701a4\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99997294\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"61160fc8c892b414\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nHow to Install the ClawHub Extension for OpenClaw - YouTube\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"61160fc8c892b414\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=s_PewdrjlVY\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9e738bec8b1617cf\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nInstall ClawHub extension for OpenClaw to access hundreds of AI skills ... OpenClaw agent with powerful skills from ClawHub repository.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9e738bec8b1617cf\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.99996734\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"256e1d51859fd4bd\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nA Guide to Installing OpenClaw Skills and Practical Applications\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"256e1d51859fd4bd\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.tencentcloud.com/techpedia/139672\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a776d5962a6fd803\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nTo allow everyone to quickly experience the capabilities of **OpenClaw + Skills**, we have integrated a browser operation plugin, `agent-browser v0.2.0`, into the latest version of the OpenClaw application template. You can also install the Skills you want to use directly through a chat with OpenClaw. Then refer to the instruction below to tell OpenClaw which Skill you want to install:. Of course, you can also verify the successful installation by having OpenClaw check the usage instructions for the Skill:. First, let’s have OpenClaw check the currently installed Skills:. You've deployed OpenClaw, connected a messaging channel, and installed a couple of skills. OpenClaw (often deployed as Clawdbot) is a pragmatic way to build these systems: you combine skills, triggers, and policies so routine operations run consistently, while humans stay in control of approvals and. OpenClaw (often deployed as Clawdbot) is a pragmatic way to build those workflows: you combine skills, triggers, and policies so that routine operations can run consistently, while humans stay in control of approvals and exceptions.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"a776d5962a6fd803\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.9999615\n    },